{"title_page": "Noel Kaseke", "text_new": "{{short description|Zimbabwean footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Noel Kaseke\n| image = Noel Kaseke (Omonia Nicosia).JPG\n| image_size = 200\n| caption = Kaseke playing for [[AC Omonia]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.78}}\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1980|12|24}}\n| birth_place = [[Bulawayo]], [[Zimbabwe]]\n| currentclub =   \n| clubnumber =  \n| position = [[Midfielder (association football)|Defensive Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = 1999\u20132002 \n| years2 = 2002\u20132003 \n| years3 = 2003 \n| years4 = 2003\u20132004 \n| years5 = 2004\u20132007 \n| years6 = 2007\u20132012\n| years7 = 2012\u20132013\n| years8 = 2013\n| years9 = 2014\u20132016\n| years10 = 2016\u20132018\n| clubs1 = [[Highlanders FC]] \n| clubs2 = [[KF Erzeni Shijak]] \n| clubs3 = [[Highlanders FC]] \n| clubs4 = [[Mohun Bagan AC]] \n| clubs5 = [[Enosis Neon Paralimni]] \n| clubs6 = [[AC Omonia]]\n| clubs7 = [[Alki Larnaca F.C.|Alki Larnaca]]\n| clubs8 = [[Al-Shaab CSC|Al-Shaab]]\n| clubs9 = [[Dibba Al-Hisn Sports Club|Dibba Al-Hisn]]\n| clubs10 = [[Masfut Club|Masfut]]\n| caps1 = 101  \n| caps2 = 22  \n| caps3 = 4  \n| caps4 = 12  \n| caps5 = 73  \n| caps6 = 118\n| caps7 = 15\n| caps8 = 11\n| goals1 = 16  \n| goals2 = 4  \n| goals3 = 0  \n| goals4 = 5  \n| goals5 = 4  \n| goals6 = 4 \n| goals7 = 0 \n| goals8 = 1\n| nationalyears1 = 2007\u2013\n| nationalteam1 = [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 7  \n| nationalgoals1 = 0 \n| club-update = June 3, 2013\n| nationalteam-update = April 7, 2013\n}}\n\n'''Noel Kaseke''' (born December 24, 1980 in [[Bulawayo]], [[Zimbabwe]]) is a Zimbabwean [[football (soccer)|football]] [[midfielder]]. He currently plays as a [[Midfielder (association football)|defensive midfielder]] . \n\nKaseke grew up in [[Dete]] and attended secondary school at [[Marist Brothers Dete]].\n\nKaseke started his senior footballing career in the [[Highlanders FC]] in 1999. Three years later he moved for the first time to Europe, and joined the [[KF Erzeni Shijak]] in Albania. Then he returned to Highlanders FC for six months. He also played in [[Mohun Bagan AC]] in India. His next club was [[Enosis Neon Paralimni]] where he stayed for three years. In June 2007 he signed a contract with [[AC Omonia]]. He plays best as a defensive midfielder but he also plays well as a right back. In May 2012 his contract with [[AC Omonia]] end, so Kaseke was free to find his new team. During this five years with [[AC Omonia]] Kaseke won 5 titles.\n\n==Honours==\n'''[[AC Omonia|Omonia]]'''\n*[[Cypriot First Division|Cypriot Championship]]: [[Cypriot First Division 2009-10|2010]]\n*[[Cypriot Cup]]: [[2010\u201311 Cypriot Cup|2011]], [[2011\u201312 Cypriot Cup|2012]]\n*[[LTV Super Cup|Cyprus FA Shield]]: [[LTV Super Cup|2010]]\n\n==External links==\n* {{NFT player|pid=30337}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kaseke, Noel}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Bulawayo]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean footballers]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwe international footballers]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:AC Omonia players]]\n[[Category:Alki Larnaca FC players]]\n[[Category:Enosis Neon Paralimni FC players]]\n[[Category:Al-Shaab CSC players]]\n[[Category:Dibba Al-Hisn Sports Club players]]\n[[Category:Masfout Club players]]\n[[Category:Cypriot First Division players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Cyprus]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Albania]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:Highlanders F.C. players]]\n[[Category:UAE Division 1 players]]\n[[Category:UAE Pro League players]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n{{Zimbabwe-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Noel Kaseke\n| image = Noel Kaseke (Omonia Nicosia).JPG\n| image_size = 200\n| caption = Kaseke playing for [[AC Omonia]]\n| height = {{height|m=