{"title_page": "Tapuwa Kapini", "text_new": "{{short description|Zimbabwean footballer}}\n{{EngvarB|date=May 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Tapuwa Kapini\n| fullname = Tapuwa Kapini\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1984|7|17}}\n| birth_place = [[Harare]], [[Zimbabwe]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.78}}\n| position    = goalkeeper\n| currentclub  = [[Highlands Park]]\n| clubnumber  = \n| years1 = 2001\u20132006 \n| years2 = 2006\u20132011 \n| years3 = 2011\u20132015\n| years4 = 2015\u2013\n| clubs1 = [[Highlanders FC]] \n| clubs2 = [[Platinum Stars]] \n| clubs3 = [[AmaZulu F.C. (South Africa)|AmaZulu]]\n| clubs4 = [[Highlands Park]]\n| caps1  = 0 | goals1 = 0 \n| caps2 = 82 | goals2 = 0 \n| caps3 = 61 | goals3 = 0\n| caps4 = 28 | goals4 = 1 \n| nationalyears1 =\n| nationalteam1 = [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 31\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate = 31 October 2018\n| ntupdate = 31 October 2018\n}}\n\n'''Tapuwa Kapini''' is a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|football goalkeeper]] and member of the [[Zimbabwe national football team]]. He plays for [Highlands Park F.C. (South Africa)|in the South African [[Premier Soccer League]].\nHis first club was [[Black Aces, Zimbabwe]].<ref>[http://www.mtnfootball.com/live/content.php?Item_ID=7289&Revision=en%2F10 MTNfootball.com \u2013 Player Profile: Tapuwa Kapini (Zimbabwe)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\nOn 10 February 2015, Kapini join [[Highlands Park]] on a free transfer.\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201502110454.html|title=Zimbabwe: Kapini Quits Amazulu for Division One Side|date=2015-02-11|work=New Zimbabwe (London)|access-date=2018-05-18}}</ref>\n\n<ref>https://www.footballdatabase.eu/en/player/details/5648-tapuwa-kapini</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NFT player|pid=7402}}\n\n{{AmaZulu}}\n{{Zimbabwe Squad 2004 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n{{Zimbabwe Squad 2006 Africa Cup of N